Date: 2026-03-20
Description: Implements SPHERE (Spatial Poisson Hierarchical modEl with 
    pathway-infoRmed gEne networks), a Bayesian spatial Poisson log-normal 
    model for identifying spatially expressed (SE) genes in spatial 
    transcriptomics data. SPHERE jointly captures spatial dependence across 
    tissue locations and gene-level dependence informed by biological pathways 
    via a pathway-informed conditional autoregressive (CAR) prior. The 
    hierarchical framework enables simultaneous detection of clusters of SE 
    and non-SE genes while borrowing strength across related genes.
